snippet.title: Superman | Official Trailer | DC
snippet.description:
Your choices, your actions, that‚Äôs what makes you who you are. #Superman - Only In Theaters and @Imax July 11

‚ÄúSuperman,‚Äù DC Studios‚Äô first feature film to hit the big screen, is set to soar into theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures.  In his signature style, James Gunn takes on the original superhero in the newly imagined DC universe with a singular blend of epic action, humor and heart, delivering a Superman who‚Äôs driven by compassion and an inherent belief in the goodness of humankind. 

DC Studios heads Peter Safran and Gunn are producing the film, which Gunn directs from his own screenplay, based on characters from DC, Superman created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.

The film stars David Corenswet (‚ÄúTwisters,‚Äù ‚ÄúHollywood‚Äù) in the dual role of Superman/Clark Kent, Rachel Brosnahan (‚ÄúThe Marvelous Mrs. Maisel‚Äù) as Lois Lane and Nicholas Hoult (the ‚ÄúX-Men‚Äù movies, ‚ÄúJuror #2‚Äù) as Lex Luthor.  The film also stars Edi Gathegi (‚ÄúFor All Mankind‚Äù), Anthony Carrigan (‚ÄúBarry,‚Äù ‚ÄúGotham‚Äù), Nathan Fillion (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad‚Äù), Isabela Merced (‚ÄúAlien Romulus‚Äù), Skyler Gisondo (‚ÄúLicorice Pizza,‚Äù ‚ÄúBooksmart‚Äù), Sara Sampaio (‚ÄúAt Midnight‚Äù), Mar√≠a Gabriela de Far√≠a (‚ÄúThe Moodys‚Äù), Wendell Pierce (‚ÄúSelma,‚Äù ‚ÄúTom Clancy‚Äôs Jack Ryan‚Äù), Alan Tudyk (‚ÄúAndor‚Äù), Pruitt Taylor Vince (‚ÄúBird Box‚Äù) and Neva Howell (‚ÄúGreedy People‚Äù).

‚ÄúSuperman‚Äù is executive produced by Nikolas Korda, Chantal Nong Vo and Lars Winther.  Behind the camera, Gunn is joined by frequent collaborators, including director of photography Henry Braham, production designer Beth Mickle, costume designer Judianna Makovsky and composer John Murphy, along with composer David Fleming (‚ÄúThe Last of Us‚Äù) and editors William Hoy (‚ÄúThe Batman‚Äù) and Craig Alpert (‚ÄúDeadpool 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlue Beetle‚Äù).  

DC Studios Presents a Troll Court Entertainment/The Safran Company Production, A James Gunn Film, ‚ÄúSuperman,‚Äù which will be in theaters and IMAX¬Æ nationwide on July 11, 2025, and internationally beginning 9 July 2025, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures.

snippet.title: Kya Jo Hota Hai Woh Ache Ke Liye Hota Hai? By Sandeep Maheshwari
snippet.description:
Sandeep Maheshwari is a name among millions who struggled, failed and surged ahead in search of success, happiness and contentment. Just like any middle class guy, he too had a bunch of unclear dreams and a blurred vision of his goals in life. All he had was an undying learning attitude to hold on to. Rowing through ups and downs, it was time that taught him the true meaning of his life.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

en-IN.description:
Gokuldham Society | Gada Electronics | Bonus | Financial Year

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge?

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.title: Serious Unemployment Problem | Dreamz Unlimited
snippet.description:
We often complain that there are no opportunities to earn a decent living in our state apart from government jobs. But if we look around us, the reality tells a different story. Every day, we see thousands of people from outside the state coming here and earning a good income through various kinds of work, be it small businesses, manual labor, services, or trade. These opportunities are not hidden; they are right in front of our eyes. Yet, we tend to overlook them, thinking they are either beneath us or not worth pursuing.

It is important to understand that it is not the outsiders‚Äô fault for seizing these chances. In fact, they are simply making the most of the opportunities that we ourselves have ignored or failed to recognize. The real issue lies with us, we have become too dependent on limited pathways like government employment, and in doing so, we have allowed others to step in and fill the gap.

The problem is not the lack of opportunity, but our mindset. We need to change the way we look at work and income. We must begin to value dignity in all forms of labor and open our eyes to the many possibilities around us. Instead of complaining, let us take responsibility and start building something for ourselves, in our own land. It's time we rise to the occasion and reclaim the opportunities that are ours to begin with.
This video is just a small satire take on it.

snippet.title: Android 16 FIRST LOOK - Totally Changed !
snippet.description:
naya saal naya maal

üî• Subscribe for Tabahi Videos

Android 16 is the next major leap in Google‚Äôs mobile OS, bringing a wave of AI-powered features, privacy upgrades, and performance improvements to Android smartphones in 2025. With a strong focus on context-aware intelligence, cross-device fluidity, and smoother multitasking, Android 16 is designed to power the next generation of smartphones, tablets, and foldables.

üîç Top Features of Android 16:

Gemini AI Integration: Smart reply, live summarization, AI-assisted typing, and app-aware suggestions built into the OS.

Lock Screen Widgets 2.0: Deeper customization, glanceable info, and always-on productivity.

Better Background Activity Control: Improved battery life with smarter app hibernation and process management.

Privacy Dashboard 2.0: Real-time app access tracking for microphone, camera, and location usage.

Universal App Streaming: Continue apps seamlessly across Android, ChromeOS, and Windows.

AI-Powered Multilingual Typing: Automatically detects and adapts to the language you‚Äôre typing in without switching keyboards.

Revamped Material You Design: Even more dynamic theming, contrast improvements, and adaptive animations.

Improved Foldable & Tablet Support: Enhanced taskbar, split-screen gestures, and large-screen app optimizations.

Android 16 will begin rolling out in beta versions by mid-2025, with the Pixel 9 series and top flagships from Samsung, OnePlus, iQOO, and Vivo among the first to get it.

If you're searching for Android 16 features list, Android 16 eligible devices, or wondering how it compares to iOS 18, this deep dive covers everything you need to know about Google's most intelligent Android version yet.

As she tries to express her feelings, he consistently pushes her away, burdened by family responsibilities and hesitant to get entangled in a complicated romance. All of this is happening in a delightful, coming-of-age manner.

snippet.description:
Gokuldham Society | Gada Electronics | Bonus | Financial Year

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge? 

 Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  #GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame


Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.title: LIVE: PM Modi's address to the nation
snippet.description:
In his address to the nation about Operation Sindoor, PM Modi described it as an unwavering pledge for justice. He thundered that the terrorists dared to wipe the Sindoor from the foreheads of our sisters; that's why India destroyed the very headquarters of terror. The PM highlighted that Operation Sindoor has redefined the fight against terror. He concluded by saying terror & talks cannot coexist and water & blood can never flow together.

snippet.title: Nobody 2 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Nobody ruins his vacation. #Nobody2 hits theaters August 15.

---
Sometimes the most dangerous place for a dad is a family vacation.

Bob Odenkirk returns as suburban husband, father and workaholic assassin Hutch
Mansell in the new chapter to Nobody, the hit 2021 bare-knuckle action-thriller that
opened at number one at the U.S. box office.

Four years after he inadvertently took on the Russian mob, Hutch remains $30 million in debt to the criminal organization and is working it off with an unending string of hits on international thugs.

Much as he likes the slam-bang action of his ‚Äújob,‚Äù Hutch and his wife Becca
(International Emmy nominee Connie Nielsen) find themselves overworked and drifting apart. So, they decide to take their kids (Gage Munroe, Paisley Cadorath) on a short getaway to Wild Bill‚Äôs Majestic Midway and Waterpark, the one and only place where Hutch and his brother Harry (Grammy and Emmy nominee RZA) went on a vacation as kids.

With Hutch‚Äôs dad (Emmy winner Christopher Lloyd) in tow, the family arrives in the small tourist town of Plummerville (‚ÄúPlummerville is Summerville!‚Äù), eager for some fun in the sun.
But when a minor encounter with some town bullies yanks the family into the crosshairs of a corrupt theme-park operator (John Ortiz; Fast and Furious franchise, Bumblebee) and his shady sheriff (Emmy and Golden Globe nominee Colin Hanks), Hutch finds himself the focus of the most unhinged, blood-thirsty crime boss he (or anyone) has ever encountered (Emmy winning and Oscar¬Æ nominated screen icon, Sharon Stone).

Nobody 2 is an 87North/Eighty Two Films/Odenkirk Provissiero Entertainment
production, directed by Timo Tjahjanto (The Night Comes for Us, The Big 4). The
screenplay is by returning writer Derek Kolstad (John Wick, Die Hart) and by Aaron
Rabin (Tom Clancy‚Äôs Jack Ryan), from a story by Derek Kolstad, based on characters created by Derek Kolstad. This film‚Äôs returning producers are 87North founders Kelly McCormick (Bullet Train, The Fall Guy) and David Leitch (Bullet Train, The Fall Guy); Odenkirk Provissiero Entertainment founder Marc Provissiero (No Hard Feelings, PEN15), Eighty Two Films founder Braden Aftergood (Hell or High Water, Samaritan); and Bob Odenkirk (Better Call Saul, Breaking Bad). The executive producer is David Hyman.

snippet.title: AI World in 2035: Tesla VP Ashok Elluswamy‚Äôs Bold Prediction | Gobinath
snippet.description:
Enquiries:
talk2gobinath@gmail.com

Stay ahead with direct updates from Gobinath ‚Äî interviews, insights, and powerful voices.
Join the official WhatsApp Channel today:
https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Vb5gNn82Jl8DSfwhUM3G

#Gobinath #ashokelluswamy #tesla #elonmusk #ai #artificialintelligence #ev #evcars #roboticsengineering #podcast #agi #artificialgeneralintelligence #humanoidrobot #humanintelligence #adas #quantumcomputer #software #hardware 

In this groundbreaking episode, Gobinath sits down with Ashok Elluswamy, Vice President of AI Software at Tesla, for his first-ever in-depth interview. A proud Tamil native, Ashok shares his inspiring journey from his roots in Tamil Nadu to working directly with Elon Musk at one of the world‚Äôs most innovative companies.

This episode dives deep into:
 ‚Ä¢ The future of AI in education, mobility, and robotics
 ‚Ä¢ The integration of AI + EV in Tesla cars
 ‚Ä¢ Exclusive insights into Tesla‚Äôs humanoid robot program
 ‚Ä¢ Behind-the-scenes stories of working with Elon Musk‚Äîhis mindset, decisions, and brilliance
 ‚Ä¢ A vision of what‚Äôs next for AI-driven robotics and autonomous technology

If you‚Äôre passionate about AI careers, the future of robotics, or just love inspirational stories that break boundaries‚Äîdon‚Äôt miss this episode.

00:00:00 ‚Äì Show Highlights
Key moments and insights from the episode.

00:03:10 ‚Äì Guest Introduction by Gobinath
Gobinath introduces Ashok Elluswamy, setting the tone for the conversation.

00:04:10 ‚Äì Who is Ashok Elluswamy?
A deep dive into Ashok‚Äôs background and professional journey.

00:06:10 ‚Äì Software vs. Hardware in AI
Ashok shares insights on the synergy and challenges between software and hardware in AI development.

00:10:46 ‚Äì Is AI Overrated?
Ashok‚Äôs honest take on the hype vs. reality of artificial intelligence.

00:12:27 ‚Äì Ashok‚Äôs Vision for 2035
A bold prediction of how AI could shape the world by 2035.

00:16:46 ‚Äì Building an Abundant Future with AI
Exploring how AI can lead to an abundant and equitable future.

00:19:53 ‚Äì ADAS & Machine Learning
Ashok explains Advanced Driver-Assistance Systems and the role of ML in autonomous driving.

00:25:24 ‚Äì Human Driving vs. Self-Driving Cars
A comparison of human drivers and AI-driven vehicles in terms of safety and efficiency.

00:31:19 ‚Äì AI and Quantum Physics
How the future of AI intersects with the revolutionary field of quantum physics.

00:36:10 ‚Äì LIDAR and Tesla‚Äôs Self-Driving Approach
Discussing Tesla‚Äôs vision and why it diverges from LIDAR-based systems.

00:39:05 ‚Äì Ashok‚Äôs Educational Journey
The personal decisions and turning points that shaped Ashok‚Äôs academic and career path.

00:42:45 ‚Äì A Glimpse Into Ashok‚Äôs Personal Life
Ashok talks about his married life and balancing work and home.

00:43:38 ‚Äì Working Culture with Elon Musk
What it‚Äôs like to work directly with Elon Musk and the expectations at Tesla.

00:46:17 ‚Äì What‚Äôs the Point of Tesla?
Ashok articulates the core mission and long-term vision of Tesla.

00:48:46 ‚Äì The Future of Car Ownership
Will people buy more cars in the future‚Äîor fewer? Ashok shares his thoughts.

00:51:30 ‚Äì EV Market in India
A look into the Indian electric vehicle market and its global significance.

00:53:04 ‚Äì Pathway for Aspiring Engineers
Advice for young engineers aiming to follow in Ashok‚Äôs footsteps.

00:53:45 ‚Äì Outro
Closing thoughts and thanks for tuning in.

#Gobinath #ashokelluswamy #tesla #elonmusk #ai #artificialintelligence #ev #evcars #roboticsengineering #podcast #agi #artificialgeneralintelligence #humanoidrobot #humanintelligence #adas #quantumcomputer #software #hardware 

In this groundbreaking episode, Gobinath sits down with Ashok Elluswamy, Vice President of AI Software at Tesla, for his first-ever in-depth interview. A proud Tamil native, Ashok shares his inspiring journey from his roots in Tamil Nadu to working directly with Elon Musk at one of the world‚Äôs most innovative companies.

This episode dives deep into:
 ‚Ä¢ The future of AI in education, mobility, and robotics
 ‚Ä¢ The integration of AI + EV in Tesla cars
 ‚Ä¢ Exclusive insights into Tesla‚Äôs humanoid robot program
 ‚Ä¢ Behind-the-scenes stories of working with Elon Musk‚Äîhis mindset, decisions, and brilliance
 ‚Ä¢ A vision of what‚Äôs next for AI-driven robotics and autonomous technology

If you‚Äôre passionate about AI careers, the future of robotics, or just love inspirational stories that break boundaries‚Äîdon‚Äôt miss this episode.

00:00:00 ‚Äì Show Highlights
Key moments and insights from the episode.

00:03:10 ‚Äì Guest Introduction by Gobinath
Gobinath introduces Ashok Elluswamy, setting the tone for the conversation.

00:04:10 ‚Äì Who is Ashok Elluswamy?
A deep dive into Ashok‚Äôs background and professional journey.

00:06:10 ‚Äì Software vs. Hardware in AI
Ashok shares insights on the synergy and challenges between software and hardware in AI development.

00:10:46 ‚Äì Is AI Overrated?
Ashok‚Äôs honest take on the hype vs. reality of artificial intelligence.

00:12:27 ‚Äì Ashok‚Äôs Vision for 2035
A bold prediction of how AI could shape the world by 2035.

00:16:46 ‚Äì Building an Abundant Future with AI
Exploring how AI can lead to an abundant and equitable future.

00:19:53 ‚Äì ADAS & Machine Learning
Ashok explains Advanced Driver-Assistance Systems and the role of ML in autonomous driving.

00:25:24 ‚Äì Human Driving vs. Self-Driving Cars
A comparison of human drivers and AI-driven vehicles in terms of safety and efficiency.

00:31:19 ‚Äì AI and Quantum Physics
How the future of AI intersects with the revolutionary field of quantum physics.

00:36:10 ‚Äì LIDAR and Tesla‚Äôs Self-Driving Approach
Discussing Tesla‚Äôs vision and why it diverges from LIDAR-based systems.

00:39:05 ‚Äì Ashok‚Äôs Educational Journey
The personal decisions and turning points that shaped Ashok‚Äôs academic and career path.

00:42:45 ‚Äì A Glimpse Into Ashok‚Äôs Personal Life
Ashok talks about his married life and balancing work and home.

00:43:38 ‚Äì Working Culture with Elon Musk
What it‚Äôs like to work directly with Elon Musk and the expectations at Tesla.

00:46:17 ‚Äì What‚Äôs the Point of Tesla?
Ashok articulates the core mission and long-term vision of Tesla.

00:48:46 ‚Äì The Future of Car Ownership
Will people buy more cars in the future‚Äîor fewer? Ashok shares his thoughts.

00:51:30 ‚Äì EV Market in India
A look into the Indian electric vehicle market and its global significance.

00:53:04 ‚Äì Pathway for Aspiring Engineers
Advice for young engineers aiming to follow in Ashok‚Äôs footsteps.

00:53:45 ‚Äì Outro
Closing thoughts and thanks for tuning in.
